    "review_date": "2026-02-23",
    "generation_notes": "Arcane Denial oracle: 'Counter target spell. Its controller may draw up to two cards at the beginning of the next upkeep. You draw a card.' So: (1) Counter the targeted spell; (2) Arcane Denial's caster (p2) draws 1 now; (3) a delayed trigger is set up so Harmonize's controller (p1) may draw up to 2 at next upkeep. This script tests only the immediate effects (counter + p2 draws 1). The delayed upkeep trigger is noted but not executed in the script (future turn). Initial state: p1 has Harmonize in hand with {2}{G}{G} in pool; p2 has Arcane Denial with {1}{U} in pool. Sequence: p1 casts Harmonize, p2 responds with Arcane Denial, all pass, Arcane Denial resolves first (LIFO).",
